- Right.
- You know?

12:19.166 --> 12:21.000
♪ ♪

12:21.033 --> 12:23.467
- Adam, Hannah, and Wes,
meet me in the crew mess

12:23.500 --> 12:25.533
for the preference sheet
meeting.

12:27.066 --> 12:29.066
♪ ♪

12:29.100 --> 12:32.633
All right, our next charter,
the primary guests,

12:32.633 --> 12:35.500
Dr. Quang Henderson
and his wife Staci,

12:35.500 --> 12:38.200
are fixtures
on the Houston social scene

12:38.233 --> 12:40.600
and have a high expectation
when they travel.

12:40.633 --> 12:43.233
- The guests requested
a black-tie Texas-themed

12:43.266 --> 12:45.166
dinner party with tuxedos,
ball gowns,

12:45.200 --> 12:46.734
and yellow roses on the table.

12:46.767 --> 12:48.100
They look like
the kind of guests

12:48.133 --> 12:49.600
that are gonna be very...
[snaps fingers]

12:49.633 --> 12:51.333
But it's only
a one-day charter.

12:51.367 --> 12:53.100
How hard can it be?

12:53.100 --> 12:55.200
- I see a lot of spicy,
and they're from Texas,

12:55.233 --> 12:57.066
so I know Texans
can take the heat.

12:57.100 --> 12:59.467
- Dislikes onions.
- Look at that.

12:59.500 --> 13:01.333
- Don't grow your horns
on the forehead.

13:01.367 --> 13:02.700
- This shouldn't be too much
of a problem.

13:02.734 --> 13:05.467
- We're going to anchor
closer to their hotel here

13:05.500 --> 13:07.633
in Dubrovnik to pick them up.

13:07.667 --> 13:09.533
Are we good?
- Pumped.

13:09.533 --> 13:11.266
- Rock and roll.

13:11.266 --> 13:13.066
[glass squeaks]

13:13.100 --> 13:14.266
- So how's the Jacuzzi?

13:14.300 --> 13:16.533
Is it heating up
all the way to 40?

13:16.567 --> 13:18.600
- Thirties.
- Yeah.

13:20.033 --> 13:24.266
- I am fed up of watching Malia
bounce off Wes,

13:24.300 --> 13:27.533
bounce off Adam, and now
she's the lead deckhand?

13:27.567 --> 13:30.100
I mean, just stop it.

13:32.266 --> 13:35.000
[upbeat music]

13:35.033 --> 13:37.133
♪ ♪

13:37.166 --> 13:38.667
- Start pulling up
on the chain, Malia.

13:38.667 --> 13:40.600
- Copy that.

13:40.633 --> 13:42.266
- And no traffic
on starboard side.

13:42.266 --> 13:44.767
- We are all clear.
No traffic astern of us.

13:45.000 --> 13:46.066
- Well done.

13:47.400 --> 13:52.233
♪ ♪

13:52.266 --> 13:53.433
- Bugs, Bugs, Hannah?

13:53.467 --> 13:55.400
- What can I help you with,
Hannah?

13:55.433 --> 13:57.767
- Do you mind quickly
just clearing the crew mess?

13:58.000 --> 13:59.300
- Okay, copy.

13:59.300 --> 14:01.700
- [laughs]

14:01.734 --> 14:03.567
- All right.
- Bugs, go enjoy yourself.

14:03.567 --> 14:05.567
It's not really my place
as a third stewardess to, like,

14:05.567 --> 14:07.033
ask her chief stew to like,

14:07.066 --> 14:08.500
"Hey, can you work
a little harder?"

14:08.533 --> 14:11.633
I'm not gonna be the one
to criticize her work ethic.

14:11.667 --> 14:15.133
- I want to drop the starboard
anchor down to four shackles.

14:15.166 --> 14:16.433
- Copy that.
Dropping anchor.

14:16.433 --> 14:18.367
- You watch the chain.
I'll drop the shackles.

14:18.400 --> 14:20.133
- Okay.
[laughs]

14:23.700 --> 14:25.266
- Talk to me.

14:27.567 --> 14:29.166
[percussive music]

14:29.166 --> 14:31.200
How many is in the water?

14:32.467 --> 14:34.033
Put your finger up.

14:35.066 --> 14:36.400
I don't get it.

14:36.433 --> 14:37.600
Someone talk to me.

14:37.633 --> 14:39.734
I'm getting really annoyed
with the bow.

14:39.734 --> 14:41.333
- What the hell
are they doing?

14:41.367 --> 14:43.600
- That's five.
Five under.

14:43.600 --> 14:45.467
- I don't want you two
working the bow together,

14:45.500 --> 14:48.200
not for the duration
of this trip.

14:48.200 --> 14:49.433
- Copy that, Captain.

14:49.467 --> 14:51.467
- I'm annoyed
with Malia and Wes

14:51.467 --> 14:53.533
because they need
to communicate to me.

14:53.567 --> 14:55.567
Actually,
just pop in the bridge.

14:57.467 --> 14:58.667
- If she can't do the job,

14:58.700 --> 15:00.467
then I want someone up there
that can do the job.

15:00.467 --> 15:02.200
- But I--
- Especially in this.

15:02.200 --> 15:04.133
- I don't understand what
she was doing wrong, Captain.

15:04.166 --> 15:06.400
- What I want is for the person
on the bow to be able

15:06.433 --> 15:09.066
to release the anchor
and hold their hand up.

15:09.066 --> 15:12.000
If she's not tall enough, then
you put someone who's taller.

15:12.033 --> 15:13.400
- Oh, it's because
she wasn't tall enough.

15:13.433 --> 15:14.600
- I don't know.
I couldn't see her fingers.

15:14.633 --> 15:15.734
- Okay.

15:15.767 --> 15:17.100
- Now that Malia's
lead deckhand,

15:17.100 --> 15:18.367
she needs to step it up
and take charge.

15:18.367 --> 15:19.433
She can't be passive
on the bow.

15:19.467 --> 15:20.433
She has to speak up.

15:20.467 --> 15:21.734
She needs to own it.

15:21.767 --> 15:23.033
- She said
that you were too short,

15:23.066 --> 15:24.433
and she couldn't see
your fingers.

15:24.467 --> 15:26.567
- [laughs]
- Yeah.

15:26.600 --> 15:28.367
- Okay, I'm not that short.

15:28.400 --> 15:30.033
- All crew, all crew.

15:30.066 --> 15:31.700
Guests will be arriving...

15:31.734 --> 15:33.633
in 15 minutes by water taxi.

15:33.667 --> 15:36.467
[upbeat music]

15:36.500 --> 15:39.333
♪ ♪

15:39.367 --> 15:42.333
- I am so happy right now.
- Yay!

15:44.266 --> 15:46.633
- That's awesome.
- I can't find my shoes.

15:46.633 --> 15:48.066
- It's the first pickup
that we've done

15:48.100 --> 15:49.500
where the guests
have come by water taxi,

15:49.533 --> 15:52.367
so it's a real cool entrance
coming onto this boat

15:52.400 --> 15:54.567
overlooking this amazing
fortress of Dubrovnik.

15:54.600 --> 15:56.233
- How you all doing?
- Hello.

15:56.266 --> 15:57.233
- Welcome to the yacht
"Sirocco."

15:57.266 --> 15:58.533
- Hello.

15:58.567 --> 16:00.133
- I'd like to bring you
on board.

16:00.166 --> 16:02.500
- Okay, first and foremost,
you can't speak anymore,

16:02.533 --> 16:04.100
because our women
like accents,

16:04.133 --> 16:06.000
and so you got to be quiet.

16:06.000 --> 16:07.600
- Okay.
- He looks fresh to death.

16:07.633 --> 16:09.233
- You're gonna hold me, right?
- Yep. There you go.

16:09.266 --> 16:12.133
- There we go.
- They are fancy.

16:12.166 --> 16:13.533
- Oh, my God.
- Welcome. I'm Sandy...

16:13.567 --> 16:15.400
- Hi! Staci Henderson.
- Your captain.

16:15.400 --> 16:17.133
- Quang Henderson.
Real nice to meet you.

16:17.133 --> 16:18.600
- Nice to meet you.
Welcome.

16:18.633 --> 16:20.000
- Lauren.
- Nice to meet you.

16:20.000 --> 16:21.266
- Adam, nice to meet you.

16:21.266 --> 16:22.633
These guys are dressed
to the nines.

16:22.667 --> 16:24.667
It's sort of like
the board game, Clue.

16:24.667 --> 16:26.266
It's like a murder mystery.

16:26.266 --> 16:27.633
- Welcome aboard "Sirocco."

16:27.667 --> 16:29.400
Hannah's gonna give you
a little tour,

16:29.400 --> 16:31.200
and after that we're gonna
pick up our anchor

16:31.233 --> 16:32.500
and proceed with our day.

16:32.533 --> 16:34.400
- Yay!
- Thank you, let's do this.

16:34.400 --> 16:37.033
- Let's start the tour.
This is the main salon.

16:37.066 --> 16:38.367
- It's really beautiful.

16:38.400 --> 16:39.767
- Obviously one
of the very important parts

16:40.000 --> 16:41.367
on any yacht, the bar.

16:41.400 --> 16:42.700
- Hannah knows us very well.

16:42.700 --> 16:44.233
- The dog is in here.

16:44.266 --> 16:47.033
- Malia, how you gonna
get over that pile?

16:47.033 --> 16:48.633
- I'm not.

16:48.667 --> 16:52.300
- Wow, this is so awesome!

16:52.300 --> 16:53.567
- This will do.

16:53.567 --> 16:55.233
- I'll show you
the cabins downstairs.

16:55.266 --> 16:56.567
- These are pretty.
They don't need that.

16:56.600 --> 16:58.533
- If the rooms are rocking,
don't bother knocking.

17:00.700 --> 17:03.433
- We making the sushi.
- I love salmon sushi.

17:03.433 --> 17:04.633
- We've got
a massive dinner planned,

17:04.667 --> 17:06.166
so instead of a sit-down lunch,

17:06.200 --> 17:08.233
we're gonna do more of a sushi,
appetizers,

17:08.266 --> 17:11.433
tapas, kind of real light,
simple stuff.

17:11.433 --> 17:14.667
- Anchor's coming up.
- Transom on deck.

17:14.700 --> 17:16.433
- Anchor is now clear
of obstructions,

17:16.467 --> 17:17.667
and we bring her home.

17:17.700 --> 17:18.667
- Thank you.

17:18.700 --> 17:21.400
♪ ♪

17:21.433 --> 17:22.734
- Close up.
- Thank you.

17:22.734 --> 17:23.734
- Is it her margarita?
- Yes.

17:23.767 --> 17:25.200
- Oh, excellent.
- All right.

17:25.233 --> 17:27.467
- Can I get an iced coffee?
- Yes, of course.

17:27.467 --> 17:32.200
- Just with a frothed coconut
creamer and a little honey?

17:32.200 --> 17:33.667
- Yeah,
and a little honey as well?

17:33.700 --> 17:35.300
- Where is your pajamas?

17:35.333 --> 17:36.734
- I left my pajamas
on the bed.

17:36.767 --> 17:38.734
- Okay, so her pajamas need
to be steamed as well.

17:38.734 --> 17:40.033
- Okay, sure.

17:40.066 --> 17:41.166
I can already tell
this is gonna be

17:41.200 --> 17:43.600
one long one-day charter.

17:43.600 --> 17:45.467
- Actually, do you have any--
do you have any nuts?

17:45.500 --> 17:48.033
- Yes, of course.
- Okay, that'd be great.

17:48.066 --> 17:50.467
♪ ♪

17:50.467 --> 17:52.300
- Bobby and Malia.

17:52.333 --> 17:54.333
Could you go
and unpack the master for me?

17:54.333 --> 17:55.700
- Sure.

17:55.734 --> 17:58.133
[music slowing down]

17:58.166 --> 18:01.300
- Uh... like, what?
- Do we just get in there?

18:01.333 --> 18:02.500
- I don't know.
Just get in their sh--

18:02.533 --> 18:04.333
and take it all apart?

18:04.367 --> 18:05.500
- I'm lost.

18:05.533 --> 18:08.500
Like, I have no clue
how to even start.

18:08.533 --> 18:11.100
I've never even been
in the master bedroom.

18:11.100 --> 18:13.100
- Okay, those are
some titty things.

18:13.100 --> 18:15.633
- Those are nip covers.
[laughs]

18:15.633 --> 18:18.633
♪ ♪

18:18.633 --> 18:20.500
- Can we eat
down at the dining table?

18:20.533 --> 18:22.233
- To eat downstairs,
like a proper sit-up?

18:22.266 --> 18:26.367
- Yes, please.
- Okay. Hannah, Hannah.

18:26.367 --> 18:27.367
- Go ahead.

18:27.400 --> 18:28.500
- Hannah, the guests would like

18:28.533 --> 18:30.500
proper sit-down lunch

18:30.533 --> 18:32.200
on the bridge deck aft.

18:32.233 --> 18:33.734
- Saw that coming a mile away.

18:33.767 --> 18:35.200
- If everything else
wasn't enough,

18:35.233 --> 18:36.767
they now want
a sit-down lunch?

18:37.000 --> 18:38.367
This is a disaster.

18:38.367 --> 18:40.767
- All the stuff is prepared
to be individuals.

18:41.000 --> 18:42.467
You can't, like,
silver-serve a canapé.

18:42.500 --> 18:44.667
- We don't have a choice.

18:44.700 --> 18:46.400
♪ ♪

18:46.433 --> 18:48.100
- Coming up...

18:48.133 --> 18:49.367
- Don't you feel like we're
doing a lot of extra work?

18:49.400 --> 18:50.500
It's kind of annoying

18:50.533 --> 18:52.266
that, like,
Hannah gets all the credit.

18:52.300 --> 18:53.667
- Oh, you're only
noticing this now?

18:53.667 --> 18:55.734
Hannah has been this way
from day one.

18:55.767 --> 18:57.500
Your point's very valid.

19:02.533 --> 19:03.000
[upbeat music]

19:04.700 --> 19:06.533
♪ ♪

19:06.533 --> 19:08.533
- Okay, so what type
of sushi is it?

19:08.533 --> 19:11.600
- Salmon, cucumber,
or spicy tuna.

19:11.633 --> 19:13.233
We thought
canapés and these snacks

19:13.266 --> 19:14.633
would be enough
to tide them over to dinner.

19:14.667 --> 19:16.767
Of course, it wasn't,
and now I'm scrambling.

19:17.000 --> 19:18.500
Not my favorite way
to start a charter.

19:19.667 --> 19:23.133
- What do you think, is it up
to your level of expectation?

19:23.133 --> 19:24.767
- This is gorgeous.

19:25.000 --> 19:26.433
- I'm just gonna go
and do water and wine service.

19:26.433 --> 19:28.567
- Bugs, would you like to do
lead service with these guys?

19:28.600 --> 19:31.033
- Sounds like a pawn-off
to me.

19:31.033 --> 19:33.033
- All right.

19:33.066 --> 19:35.300
- I'm always willing
to take over lead service,

19:35.333 --> 19:38.300
but I kind of feel
that Hannah's just too quick

19:38.333 --> 19:39.567
to give up
her responsibilities.

19:39.600 --> 19:41.166
- Would you like pinot grigio?

19:41.166 --> 19:43.133
- Yes, that's my
favorite, actually.

19:43.166 --> 19:45.233
- Is that good?
- Yes, perfect.

19:46.567 --> 19:48.567
- Oh, no,
that's for you to taste it.

19:48.567 --> 19:50.400
- Oh.
- It's customary.

19:50.433 --> 19:52.300
- Just to taste?

19:52.300 --> 19:54.567
- Did you really
just say that?

19:54.600 --> 19:56.033
- You really don't need
any more than that, actually.

19:56.066 --> 19:58.400
- You should actually--
- Shut up, Brian.

19:58.433 --> 20:00.266
- Can I ask you a question?
- Yes.

20:00.300 --> 20:02.300
- Do you have
a travel agent on board?

20:02.300 --> 20:03.700
- A travel agent?

20:03.734 --> 20:06.166
- We need somebody to help us
book a flight to Spain.

20:06.200 --> 20:07.333
- I personally recommend

20:07.333 --> 20:09.266
either San Sebastian
or Valencia.

20:09.300 --> 20:10.567
- Can you see
what you can get us

20:10.600 --> 20:12.133
for a direct flight to either?

20:12.166 --> 20:13.734
And also, we were looking
at chartering a plane.

20:13.734 --> 20:15.066
- Okay.

20:15.066 --> 20:16.734
I'm now
a f---ing travel agent?

20:16.767 --> 20:19.266
Call me HannahBooking.com.

20:19.300 --> 20:20.333
- I haven't eaten all day

20:20.367 --> 20:23.700
except
for some nuts and cheese.

20:23.734 --> 20:25.200
- You can roll up the sushi.

20:25.233 --> 20:28.734
- Sushi roll.
Ha-ha.

20:28.734 --> 20:30.333
Delicious sushi.

20:30.333 --> 20:31.600
- I'm gonna be full today.

20:31.600 --> 20:37.467
♪ ♪

20:37.467 --> 20:39.533
Oh, my God.
How wonderful is that?

20:39.567 --> 20:41.667
- Hey, this is just lunch,
by the way.

20:41.700 --> 20:44.533
♪ ♪

20:44.567 --> 20:45.734
- Lauren, Lauren, Hannah?

20:45.767 --> 20:47.734
- Go ahead, Hannah.

20:48.000 --> 20:50.467
- Can you just pop to
the bridge for a sec, please?

20:50.500 --> 20:51.467
- Copy.

20:51.500 --> 20:53.066
♪ ♪

20:53.100 --> 20:54.300
- Can you go and unpack

20:54.333 --> 20:57.367
the starboard
forward cabin for me?

20:57.400 --> 20:59.567
I'm just booking flights
for the guests at the moment.

20:59.600 --> 21:00.767
- Okay.
- Thank you.

21:01.000 --> 21:02.633
And then just keep coming
to Bugs and asking her

21:02.633 --> 21:05.467
what she needs
for the next 2 1/2 hours, okay?

21:05.500 --> 21:06.767
- Okay.
- Thanks.

21:07.000 --> 21:08.300
- Hannah does more
talking than working.

21:08.333 --> 21:10.200
"I'm working so hard.
I'm working so hard.

21:10.233 --> 21:12.367
I'm doing all this
that you don't know about."

21:12.400 --> 21:14.500
It's like, I don't know how
long it takes to book flights,

21:14.533 --> 21:15.600
but two hours?

21:17.500 --> 21:18.500
- Why are you unpacking
the woman's,

21:18.533 --> 21:20.066
I'm unpacking the man's?

21:20.100 --> 21:21.600
♪ ♪

21:21.633 --> 21:22.767
- Oh, that's fabulous.
- Mm.

21:22.767 --> 21:25.700
- Try the tuna.
- Where do you put hats?

21:25.734 --> 21:28.033
Where do we put shoes?

21:28.066 --> 21:29.734
♪ ♪

21:29.767 --> 21:32.400
- Hey, guys, I'm gonna
get Lauren to do this.

21:32.433 --> 21:33.767
Can you help us
in the galley rather?

21:34.000 --> 21:35.533
- Yeah, copy that.
- It just makes more sense.

21:35.533 --> 21:36.533
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

21:36.533 --> 21:37.667
- We completely agree.

21:37.667 --> 21:39.000
- Nothing's helping
the situation

21:39.033 --> 21:40.133
with Bobby and Malia

21:40.166 --> 21:42.066
up in the master cabin
unpacking.

21:42.100 --> 21:44.266
They are deckhands
for a reason,

21:44.266 --> 21:45.500
and Hannah should know better.

21:45.533 --> 21:47.066
- I put, like,
the chick's on the left.

21:47.100 --> 21:48.600
Guy's on the right.
- I'll take care of it.

21:48.633 --> 21:50.066
Thank you.

21:50.100 --> 21:52.233
♪ ♪

21:52.266 --> 21:54.066
- Did you find a flight?

21:54.100 --> 21:56.533
- Yeah, but it's three stops,
so they won't take it.

21:56.567 --> 21:58.000
Um, I just wanted
to let you know,

21:58.033 --> 21:59.367
I've looked into that flight,

21:59.400 --> 22:03.367
but commercially,
it's 13 hours and 20 minutes.

22:03.400 --> 22:05.667
Dubrovnik to Zurich,
and then Zurich to Madrid.

22:05.667 --> 22:07.400
- Can we find something
that's direct?

22:07.433 --> 22:09.467
Where can we go
that's direct and that's warm?

22:09.500 --> 22:11.433
Anywhere if it's warm.

22:11.467 --> 22:14.700
- Okay, so let's do direct
from Dubrovnik to Malta.

22:14.700 --> 22:17.433
- Thank you so much.
- Okay, sure.

22:17.433 --> 22:20.433
- I think I see
a beach around this corner.

22:20.433 --> 22:22.567
You want to keep a lookout?

22:22.600 --> 22:25.633
- [whistling]

22:25.667 --> 22:27.166
♪ ♪

22:27.166 --> 22:28.166
- Can you see,
through the binoculars,

22:28.166 --> 22:30.767
a little hint of green?

22:31.000 --> 22:32.500
- I feel like
now that Malia's lead deckhand,

22:32.533 --> 22:34.433
I'm just invisible
to Captain Sandy,

22:34.467 --> 22:36.100
and that pisses me off.

22:36.133 --> 22:38.567
♪ ♪

22:38.567 --> 22:40.367
- I just got pulled aside.
- Uh-huh?

22:40.400 --> 22:42.033
- She's like,
"I don't want to do a stopover.

22:42.033 --> 22:43.166
"I want direct.

22:43.200 --> 22:45.033
Somewhere for five days
in the sun."

22:45.033 --> 22:47.567
- Did it sound like that
when it came out of her mouth?

22:47.567 --> 22:49.567
- I don't know.
It did in my head, though.

22:49.567 --> 22:51.300
- Okay.
- It kind of went in there.

22:51.333 --> 22:53.200
- All right.

22:53.233 --> 22:54.533
- Adam and I, I feel like
we've built a bridge

22:54.567 --> 22:55.600
since our heart-to-heart,

22:55.600 --> 22:58.400
and we're finally
getting along.

22:58.433 --> 23:00.333
♪ ♪

23:00.333 --> 23:01.467
- How are the ladies doing?
Are you well?

23:01.467 --> 23:02.734
- So nice.
- Awesome.

23:02.734 --> 23:04.433
- Thank you.

23:04.467 --> 23:07.567
- You know what they say
about pineapple, girls.

23:07.600 --> 23:10.700
[laughter]

23:10.734 --> 23:13.166
- Wait, what do they say
about pineapple?

23:15.066 --> 23:16.600
- Oh.
[laughs]

23:16.633 --> 23:18.000
- Did you just cut
your hand on that?

23:18.033 --> 23:20.000
- Yeah, I went to look
